This paper discusses attacks and defenses related to website fingerprinting, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves measuring and analyzing data, which falls under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of statistical methods to analyze the data, which falls under the category of statistics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves network security and privacy, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
